  "body": "# Abstract\r\n\r\nI know that there are different chains that are using Ethereum protocol (The most known is ETC. UBQ and Expanse are Ethereum forks as well.) It means that it is possible to run SWARM with side chain nodes.\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\nTo be honest, I don't see any reason in running a separate version of the whole SWARM for each Ethereum chain branch (fork). All users can use the same addresses on all Ethereum chains. It would be great if SWARM nodes could use common storage (sync with each other) but have different incentivisation system.\r\n\r\nIt would be possible to run nodes that will operate with multiple chains (this nodes should accept payments in different currencies). If a SWARM node is running in `-classic` mode then an owner of this node will receive payments in ETH for providing a data that is paid with ETH. The owner of this node will also receive payments in ETC for providing a data that is paid with ETC. Fortunately the owner of the node can use the same hex address for all types of payments.\r\n\r\nIf the node only works in ETH mode, then it will lose the ability to receive payments in ETC to store data that will be paid by ETC.\r\n\r\nIf someone wants to upload data to SWARM then this person can choose what currency would be used. A SWARM node with matching currency support and closest address would be chosen to accept data.\r\n\r\n**It is important to allow SWARM nodes to operate with multiple currencies at once.**\r\n\r\n# Motivation\r\n\r\nI think that everyone will benefit from this proposal. There is no real need to have multiple versions of exactly the same software running on different chains.\r\n\r\n### SWARM adoption\r\nThe adoption of SWARM depends on how much it will be used. Ethereum CLassic community is 10% of the whole Ethereum community. Supporting ETC payments will instantly boost the adoption of the whole SWARM ecosystem by 10%.\r\n\r\n### Immediately eliminate the competitor\r\nIf SWARM would be used only with the ETH network, it will only be a matter of time when SWARM CLassic would appear. This variant is not beneficial for the whole cryptocurrency community and users. It is not a good idea to have two copies of the SWARM for each chain.\r\nI guess it's much better to merge the Ethereum community by one common storage. It will also instantly eliminate a possibility of competition between two different ecosystems.\r\n\r\n### User friendly\r\nIf you accept several currencies as payment for a service, this is obviously more convenient than only one currency anyways.",
