    "created_at": "2017-09-06T07:03:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-09-06T07:03:28Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Some still send real eth to testnet addresses by mistake...\r\n\r\nUser education will solve this problem. They will know that it's not a problem if you send ETH into testnet address because you (or the person to whom you sent the transaction) can control testnet address on ETH mainnet. As the result you can access your funds in the testnet address and there is no danger of losing money.\r\n\r\nIt's not the key point of this proposal. At least it is potentially possible between ETH and ETC.\r\nFrom the ideological point of view, it's better to have one storage instead of implementing SWARM for each of the Ethereum-based chains, I believe. This seems to be better solution for the entire crypto-currency ecosystem.",
