    "created_at": "2018-08-08T18:19:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-08-08T18:19:43Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The SWAP protocol is strictly between two connected peers. They can settle their debts as they see fit using whatever chain they want.\r\nThis is also mentioned here: https://github.com/ethersphere/go-ethereum/issues/219#issuecomment-384689423\r\n\r\nLong term storage incentives could be more difficult to manage as would things like proof-of-burn spam protections for which every node in the network would have to be able to validate the proof and thus be connected to the same chain.\r\n\r\n I suggest we move this discussion over to ethersphere where the Swap protocol is currently being (re)implemented. https://github.com/ethersphere/go-ethereum/labels/swap",
